MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION CONDITIONS

The following attribution conditions are NON-NEGOTIABLE and must be satisfied
at all times. Failure to comply constitutes copyright infringement and a
material breach of this License.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 1 — PROJECT README ATTRIBUTION (Public Repositories)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you distribute, publish, or publicly host a project that includes this
software or any portion of it, your project's README (or equivalent primary
documentation file) MUST contain a clearly visible attribution section that
includes ALL of the following, word-for-word or substantively equivalent:

    Based on Vridhira — E-Commerce for Indian Artisans
    Original author: Himanshu (https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu)
    Source: https://github.com/vridhira/vridhira-frontend
    License: Vridhira Attribution License v1.0

This attribution must:
  • Appear in the README of your project's primary source repository.
  • Be visible without expanding collapsed sections or hidden elements.
  • Include working hyperlinks to both the author profile and the source repo.
  • Not be placed after a fold, in a footnote only, or in a file other than
    the primary documentation.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 2 — STOREFRONT UI CREDITS (Deployed Storefronts)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you deploy a live storefront (any publicly accessible website, app, or
hosted service) built on this software, the storefront MUST display visible
credits to the original project at ALL times. Specifically:

  (a) The VridhiraCredits component (located at
      src/modules/layout/components/vridhira-credits/) or equivalent visible
      UI credit block MUST remain present and rendered in the storefront
      footer or an equivalently prominent, always-visible location on every
      page of the deployed storefront.

  (b) The credits MUST link to:
        — https://github.com/vridhira/vridhira-frontend  (project source)
        — https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu  (original author)

  (c) Credits must be LEGIBLE — font size no smaller than 10px, colour
      contrast ratio of at least 3:1 against the background, and not hidden
      by CSS (display:none, visibility:hidden, opacity:0, or equivalent).

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 3 — CREDITS ARE ADDITIVE ONLY (Non-Removal Clause)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

You MAY add your own credits, branding, and attribution to the credits
section or component.

You MAY NOT:
  • Remove, replace, hide, obscure, or comment-out any existing attribution
    text, links, or copyright notices referencing Himanshu or Vridhira.
  • Rename, refactor, or restructure the VridhiraCredits component in a way
    that removes or suppresses the original attribution from the rendered UI.
  • Modify the copyright notice at the top of any source file to remove or
    alter the original author line.

You MUST treat all existing attribution as a floor — you build on top of it,
never beneath it.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 4 — COPYRIGHT NOTICE PRESERVATION (Source Files)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

All copies or substantial portions of this software — whether modified or
unmodified — MUST retain:
  • This License file in full, unmodified, in the root of the repository.
  • The copyright notice block at the top of every source file that contains
    one (Author, GitHub, Copyright, License header comments).

You may add additional copyright notices above the existing ones for your
own contributions. You may not alter or delete the existing notices.

